The paper deals with the use of machine learning for logo synthesis and manipulation, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method involves the use of clustering to stabilize GAN training, which is a graph theory and combinatorics (cs.GR) technique. The paper also discusses latent space exploration techniques, which can be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
